WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:02:13.190 --> 00:02:19.150
Episode 1

3
00:02:13.190 --> 00:02:19.150
Nice to Meet You

4
00:02:13.690 --> 00:02:17.110
What does love mean to you?

5
00:02:17.490 --> 00:02:22.660
To me, it's something you only devote
to one person in life. Your soulmate.

6
00:02:23.490 --> 00:02:27.330
So maybe I didn't show you enough love.

7
00:02:27.960 --> 00:02:34.130
Or maybe... you were never my 
soulmate in the first place.

8
00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:40.590
You're blaming this on <i>me</i>?!

9
00:02:39.090 --> 00:02:41.760
Oh, scary. A breakup fight?

10
00:02:42.050 --> 00:02:45.760
Wait, isn't that guy Hananoi-kun?

11
00:02:46.390 --> 00:02:47.930
Hananoi-kun?

12
00:02:47.930 --> 00:02:49.520
You don't know him, Hotaru?!

13
00:02:49.520 --> 00:02:52.900
Come on! The popular boy from the class
 next door whose height and looks

14
00:02:52.900 --> 00:02:55.270
everyone agrees are in the 99th percentile?

15
00:02:55.730 --> 00:03:00.360
No?! This girl couldn't care less!

16
00:03:00.360 --> 00:03:05.280
Oh, sorry. It's hard enough for me
 to remember my own classmates.

17
00:03:05.280 --> 00:03:07.290
A whole other class would be...

18
00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:09.620
It's <i>December</i> already!

19
00:03:09.620 --> 00:03:10.960
Fine then!

20
00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:14.630
You'll never be in a proper 
relationship anyway!

21
00:03:25.550 --> 00:03:29.430
I guess even hot guys go 
through horrible breakups.

22
00:03:31.350 --> 00:03:35.190
How could you say something so mean
 to someone you once liked?

23
00:03:36.190 --> 00:03:39.820
As they say, a love too strong 
can become a hate even stronger.

24
00:03:39.820 --> 00:03:43.070
You'll understand once
 you fall in love too, Hotaru.

25
00:03:43.070 --> 00:03:44.740
When you fall in love,

26
00:03:44.740 --> 00:03:48.200
your special someone becomes more
important than friends and family, right?

27
00:03:48.200 --> 00:03:51.580
I don't really get that, 
so I don't think it's for me.

28
00:03:51.580 --> 00:03:53.580
That same old excuse again?

29
00:03:53.580 --> 00:03:57.090
Well, I'd like to take this moment
 to make an announcement.

30
00:03:57.380 --> 00:04:00.260
I have a boyfriend now!

31
00:04:00.260 --> 00:04:02.420
Oh. Congrats.

32
00:04:02.420 --> 00:04:03.130
Way too sedate!

33
00:04:03.130 --> 00:04:05.140
You're supposed to get all excited!

34
00:04:05.140 --> 00:04:07.890
Or at least lament,
 "You can't leave me all alone!"

35
00:04:08.260 --> 00:04:11.020
That's kinda asking a lot, Kyo-chan.

36
00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:13.850
<i>My name is Hinase Hotaru.</i>

37
00:04:13.850 --> 00:04:17.190
<i>I'm almost sixteen, and I'm in my 
first year of high school.</i>

38
00:04:17.860 --> 00:04:21.490
<i>I've lived my life free of romance,</i>

39
00:04:18.520 --> 00:04:20.730
Anyway, thanks for listening.

40
00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:22.570
No problem. Good luck!

41
00:04:21.530 --> 00:04:24.450
<i>but I'm blessed with friends and family.</i>

42
00:04:22.570 --> 00:04:23.530
See you!

43
00:04:23.530 --> 00:04:24.740
Until next time!

44
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:30.740
<i>If I can keep spending my days peacefully,
 enjoying the little things in life,</i>

45
00:04:30.740 --> 00:04:35.330
<i>that's enough for me,
 even if I never fall in love.</i>

46
00:04:35.330 --> 00:04:39.250
<i>Or, at least, that's what I thought.</i>

47
00:04:42.630 --> 00:04:47.220
<i>No umbrella? The breakup 
must've really been a shock...</i>

48
00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:53.230
<i>I still don't get it, though. 
Why do people fall in love in the first place?</i>

49
00:04:53.810 --> 00:04:57.520
<i>What in the world does it feel like?</i>

50
00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:06.240
U-Um, you'll catch a cold like this.

51
00:05:12.580 --> 00:05:16.960
<i>I never imagined the umbrella 
I held out for him that day...</i>

52
00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:20.170
You're Hinase Hotaru-chan, right?

53
00:05:21.090 --> 00:05:22.670
Nice to meet you.

54
00:05:23.210 --> 00:05:24.420
I like you.

55
00:05:25.760 --> 00:05:27.380
Will you go out with me?

56
00:05:29.050 --> 00:05:32.600
<i>...would change my life forever.</i>

57
00:05:33.970 --> 00:05:37.100
<i>Never in my wildest dreams.</i>

58
00:05:39.100 --> 00:05:41.980
Check out that guy! Isn't he super hot?

59
00:05:44.780 --> 00:05:47.360
Hotaru-chan! Good morning.

60
00:05:47.360 --> 00:05:50.450
Hananoi-kun? G-Good morning.

61
00:05:50.820 --> 00:05:52.910
Were you waiting for me?

62
00:05:52.910 --> 00:05:53.990
Yeah.

63
00:05:53.990 --> 00:05:57.000
Even though I politely declined yesterday?

64
00:05:57.290 --> 00:06:01.670
I thought I should give you a chance
 to get to know me first.

65
00:06:06.970 --> 00:06:10.510
Hey, over there! 
Is that the girl Hananoi asked out?

66
00:06:10.510 --> 00:06:13.640
How wild is it to do that
 in front of the whole class?

67
00:06:13.640 --> 00:06:16.020
I guess hotties can get away with that stuff.

68
00:06:16.480 --> 00:06:18.890
I figured she'd be a real babe or something.

69
00:06:16.980 --> 00:06:20.310
Mind telling me about 
what sorts of things you like?

70
00:06:18.890 --> 00:06:20.850
Hey! She'll hear you!

71
00:06:21.690 --> 00:06:25.030
Hotaru-chan? Hotaru-chan?

72
00:06:25.030 --> 00:06:27.070
S-Sorry! What is it?

73
00:06:27.070 --> 00:06:30.780
Oh, I was just asking about what you're into.

74
00:06:31.070 --> 00:06:33.120
What about hairstyles and stuff?

75
00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:34.160
Hairstyles?

76
00:06:35.290 --> 00:06:38.370
I guess short hair is a lot easier to wash.

77
00:06:38.370 --> 00:06:40.040
Short hair, huh?

78
00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:42.540
Listen...

79
00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:46.050
Would you tell me why you chose me?

80
00:06:46.340 --> 00:06:51.430
When you held your umbrella out for me, 
I thought, "This girl must be my soulmate."

81
00:06:51.890 --> 00:06:54.680
You said that yesterday too.

82
00:06:57.100 --> 00:07:01.060
Well, I get approached by lots of people,

83
00:07:01.060 --> 00:07:03.690
but once we start talking,
they always drift away.

84
00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:07.190
He asked her out in front of everyone.

85
00:07:04.690 --> 00:07:09.740
They find me strange or creepy. 
I guess they get disillusioned.

86
00:07:07.190 --> 00:07:08.740
She's not what I expected at all!

87
00:07:09.740 --> 00:07:14.580
People like the way I look, so they have 
all these weird expectations of me.

88
00:07:15.240 --> 00:07:20.710
And then there was you, Hotaru-chan,
who just talked to me like it was no big deal.

89
00:07:22.460 --> 00:07:24.380
Maybe that's why.

90
00:07:27.090 --> 00:07:28.130
See you.

91
00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:33.760
H-Hotaru! What are you doing coming
to school with Hananoi-kun?!

92
00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:36.470
Kyo-chan, Shibamu! Good morning.

93
00:07:36.470 --> 00:07:37.220
Morning.

94
00:07:37.220 --> 00:07:39.890
What gives?! Did you decide
 to go out with him after all?

95
00:07:39.890 --> 00:07:42.230
You can't leave me all alone!

96
00:07:42.230 --> 00:07:43.480
No, no.

97
00:07:43.480 --> 00:07:45.650
Though he <i>did</i> say...

98
00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:49.610
"Why don't you get to know me first
and then think it over?"

99
00:07:49.990 --> 00:07:55.370
Huh. Well, how's it going? Has your
impression of him changed after a day?

100
00:07:55.370 --> 00:07:57.160
Hmm...

101
00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:59.540
He's kind of enigmatic.

102
00:07:59.870 --> 00:08:02.540
The Next Day

103
00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:05.130
A winter-exclusive cafeteria delicacy

104
00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:05.130
<i>Get them to go!</i>

105
00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:05.130
Back this year!
Braised Pork Buns

106
00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:07.590
That looks heavy.

107
00:08:07.590 --> 00:08:11.340
Oh, thanks. I was taking 
it to the faculty room...

108
00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:14.510
Huh?! Hananoi-kun, your hair!

109
00:08:14.930 --> 00:08:18.430
Well? Is it more to your liking now,
Hotaru-chan?

110
00:08:18.430 --> 00:08:22.060
Things to Do During Winter Break

111
00:08:18.430 --> 00:08:22.060
Wait, we weren't talking 
about <i>my</i> hair yesterday?!

112
00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:24.270
Oh, you don't like it?

113
00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:29.570
Art Club

114
00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:27.310
Did you really cut it just to suit my tastes?

115
00:08:27.310 --> 00:08:29.570
I figured I could work 
on my appearance first.

116
00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:33.700
You look totally stumped right now.

117
00:08:33.700 --> 00:08:35.570
Sorry, I honestly just...

118
00:08:35.990 --> 00:08:39.030
It's fine, it's fine.
The faculty room, right?

119
00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:40.040
I'll go with you.

120
00:08:39.030 --> 00:08:41.450
We're playing basketball in PE, right?

121
00:08:40.040 --> 00:08:42.290
Thank you. That's a huge help.

122
00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:46.130
I'm sorry, Hananoi-kun.

123
00:08:46.710 --> 00:08:49.210
I know you're doing all this for me,

124
00:08:50.380 --> 00:08:56.090
but I don't really know what it means 
to have special feelings for someone.

125
00:08:56.510 --> 00:09:00.180
I guess I'm like a robot 
or a cyborg or something.

126
00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:02.600
A robot, huh?

127
00:09:02.930 --> 00:09:06.690
Well, if you don't know what it's like,
 why not give it a try?

128
00:09:06.690 --> 00:09:07.440
Huh?

129
00:09:07.440 --> 00:09:09.730
Go out with me
 and experience it for yourself.

130
00:09:09.730 --> 00:09:13.490
Yeah. Like until Christmas or something.

131
00:09:14.360 --> 00:09:18.070
I'd just end up hurting you that way.

132
00:09:18.990 --> 00:09:21.160
People who are made like me

133
00:09:22.620 --> 00:09:25.620
have no business falling in love.

134
00:09:26.670 --> 00:09:29.340
There's no such thing as someone
who shouldn't fall in love.

135
00:09:34.590 --> 00:09:38.050
<i>He's an enigma,
but not the unsettling kind...</i>

136
00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:39.470
<i>I guess.</i>

137
00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:49.020
Sorry! I promised I'd eat lunch 
with my boyfriend today.

138
00:09:49.020 --> 00:09:51.360
And I've got a club meeting.

139
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:52.360
Sorry.

140
00:09:52.360 --> 00:09:53.610
Really sorry!

141
00:09:54.070 --> 00:09:55.900
<i>Guess I'm on my own today.</i>

142
00:09:57.280 --> 00:09:58.360
Hotaru-chan.

143
00:09:59.160 --> 00:10:01.450
Want to eat lunch together?

144
00:10:04.200 --> 00:10:06.960
<i>I-I came along without really thinking...</i>

145
00:10:04.910 --> 00:10:06.290
Hotaru-chan?

146
00:10:07.710 --> 00:10:09.540
<i>But I've already turned him down once.</i>

147
00:10:07.710 --> 00:10:09.540
Hotaru-chan?

148
00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:11.460
<i>Maybe I shouldn't be doing this.</i>

149
00:10:11.960 --> 00:10:15.050
Hotaru-chan, Hotaru-chan! Want one?

150
00:10:15.840 --> 00:10:18.840
The cafeteria's special braised pork bun?!

151
00:10:25.430 --> 00:10:26.890
Thank you!

152
00:10:26.890 --> 00:10:31.190
I bought that just for you, so help yourself.

153
00:10:35.110 --> 00:10:35.990
Here.

154
00:10:36.610 --> 00:10:38.110
Let's eat it together!

155
00:10:39.660 --> 00:10:40.860
Thanks for this.

156
00:10:42.780 --> 00:10:44.120
Yum!

157
00:10:45.700 --> 00:10:47.200
Thanks...

158
00:10:52.130 --> 00:10:53.250
Is it good?

159
00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:54.130
Yup.

160
00:10:54.500 --> 00:10:57.010
It's delicious because I'm eating it
 here with you.

161
00:10:58.590 --> 00:11:01.220
<i>Eating together makes it delicious?</i>

162
00:11:01.220 --> 00:11:03.970
<i>Yeah, I think I can understand that feeling.</i>

163
00:11:04.390 --> 00:11:06.520
Wait, your earrings...

164
00:11:06.520 --> 00:11:07.520
Oh.

165
00:11:07.930 --> 00:11:12.020
I figured you probably didn't 
care for flashy stuff like that.

166
00:11:13.060 --> 00:11:16.780
Um, actually, I meant to say this before,

167
00:11:16.780 --> 00:11:20.030
but you really don't need 
to change yourself for me.

168
00:11:20.450 --> 00:11:24.950
I think you should keep enjoying 
the things that you like.

169
00:11:26.290 --> 00:11:27.490
Okay.

170
00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:31.170
If it bothers you, 
I'll put my earrings back in.

171
00:11:31.170 --> 00:11:33.000
Huh? But...

172
00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:36.250
Oh, wait. I only have one...

173
00:11:36.250 --> 00:11:39.670
I must have dropped the other
 one somewhere. Oh well.

174
00:11:39.670 --> 00:11:41.680
What? Want me to help you look for it?

175
00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:43.970
No, it's fine. No big deal.

176
00:11:43.970 --> 00:11:45.850
One is enough, right?

177
00:11:51.770 --> 00:11:55.440
Why does he keep doing so much for me?

178
00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:57.150
You mean Hananoi-kun?

179
00:11:57.150 --> 00:12:00.570
He's trying so hard because 
he wants you to like him.

180
00:12:01.780 --> 00:12:04.950
Hey, hey! Does anyone have 
some hairpins I can borrow?

181
00:12:05.530 --> 00:12:08.040
These are all I've got. Will they do?

182
00:12:08.040 --> 00:12:11.710
You're a lifesaver! Thank you, Hinase-san!

183
00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:21.090
<i>I still feel like he's doing too much...</i>

184
00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:27.010
<i>I mean, take the earrings. They're against
 the dress code, so he must </i>really<i> like them.</i>

185
00:12:27.550 --> 00:12:31.680
<i>He doesn't think of himself enough.</i>

186
00:12:31.680 --> 00:12:33.270
<i>It worries me sometimes.</i>

187
00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:38.900
Hotaru-chan, want to walk home together?

188
00:12:39.610 --> 00:12:41.070
Hananoi-kun!

189
00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:44.360
Sorry, I have to go look 
for something on the field.

190
00:12:44.360 --> 00:12:47.200
I lost one of her hairpins! I'm so sorry!

191
00:12:47.450 --> 00:12:49.660
It's okay! Don't worry about it.

192
00:12:50.160 --> 00:12:53.710
But Hotaru-chan, it's...

193
00:12:59.250 --> 00:13:03.050
It'd be pretty difficult to find it right now.

194
00:13:03.380 --> 00:13:05.880
I'm sorry, Hinase-san! 
I'll buy you a new one!

195
00:13:06.180 --> 00:13:09.390
It's really okay! It's not your fault.

196
00:13:10.310 --> 00:13:14.890
Sorry to drag you out here. I guess 
we might as well walk home together.

197
00:13:20.570 --> 00:13:22.230
<i>I really should go look for it...</i>

198
00:13:25.780 --> 00:13:28.490
<i>I guess I'll go first thing in the morning.</i>

199
00:13:30.240 --> 00:13:31.790
Hananoi-kun

200
00:13:32.540 --> 00:13:34.160
Yes, hello?

201
00:13:34.160 --> 00:13:39.380
<i>Ah, Hotaru-chan? 
Sorry, I just have a quick question.</i>

202
00:13:39.380 --> 00:13:42.710
<i>Does the hairpin you lost have a ribbon?</i>

203
00:13:42.710 --> 00:13:45.720
No, it has a star on it.

204
00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:49.090
<i>Really? Then this isn't it...</i>

205
00:13:49.550 --> 00:13:51.810
<i>All right. Thanks.</i>

206
00:13:51.810 --> 00:13:53.890
<i>I'll see you at school tomorrow.</i>

207
00:13:53.890 --> 00:13:54.560
Wait!

208
00:13:55.680 --> 00:13:58.770
Hananoi-kun, where are you right now?

209
00:13:59.310 --> 00:14:03.230
You aren't actually at school, are you?

210
00:14:05.190 --> 00:14:06.360
<i>Nah.</i>

211
00:14:12.410 --> 00:14:15.200
Hotaru? Where are you going at this hour?

212
00:14:15.200 --> 00:14:16.250
School!

213
00:14:18.920 --> 00:14:20.080
<i>There's no way...</i>

214
00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:22.210
<i>He can't be there.</i>

215
00:14:22.630 --> 00:14:27.340
<i>No normal person would go searching 
for a single hairpin in the snow like this.</i>

216
00:14:29.300 --> 00:14:30.220
<i>But...</i>

217
00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:35.060
<i>But maybe Hananoi-kun would. He might.</i>

218
00:14:47.650 --> 00:14:48.990
Hotaru-chan?

219
00:14:49.910 --> 00:14:51.410
Shoot. You came.

220
00:14:54.660 --> 00:15:00.120
I'm sorry. I really wanted to surprise you,
 but I haven't found it yet.

221
00:15:00.370 --> 00:15:01.790
Hananoi-kun...

222
00:15:05.920 --> 00:15:10.050
I'm sorry, but I still don't get it.

223
00:15:10.050 --> 00:15:12.680
Why? Why go this far?

224
00:15:16.430 --> 00:15:17.560
Because I...

225
00:15:19.770 --> 00:15:21.850
wanted to make you smile.

226
00:15:26.690 --> 00:15:28.240
<i>That's it?</i>

227
00:15:28.860 --> 00:15:33.200
<i>Everything he's done has just been
 to make me smile?</i>

228
00:15:40.620 --> 00:15:44.420
I'll be fine, so why 
don't you head back home?

229
00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:46.630
I'm just going to check over here.

230
00:15:46.630 --> 00:15:47.630
Hananoi-kun.

231
00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:51.720
Hananoi-kun!

232
00:15:56.390 --> 00:15:59.310
Please, stop this. That's enough.

233
00:15:59.770 --> 00:16:03.440
Wow, I even get a nice hug from you.

234
00:16:06.020 --> 00:16:08.110
You big dummy!

235
00:16:10.110 --> 00:16:11.570
Look.

236
00:16:11.570 --> 00:16:14.280
If you make yourself sick finding it,

237
00:16:14.280 --> 00:16:16.990
I won't be happy at all!

238
00:16:17.950 --> 00:16:22.290
Oh... I see. I guess you have a point.

239
00:16:22.710 --> 00:16:24.330
I'm being weird, huh?

240
00:16:25.540 --> 00:16:27.750
People tell me I go too far.

241
00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:29.590
That's not the point!

242
00:16:29.590 --> 00:16:33.010
If you don't stop now, 
Hananoi-kun, you could die!

243
00:16:33.760 --> 00:16:35.010
Hotaru-chan...

244
00:16:35.720 --> 00:16:37.970
This isn't going to kill me.

245
00:16:37.970 --> 00:16:39.520
Besides,

246
00:16:39.810 --> 00:16:43.270
if I got to see you smile, 
then at least I'd die happy.

247
00:16:46.150 --> 00:16:51.280
If it means only one person gets to be happy,
then I don't ever want to fall in love!

248
00:16:57.780 --> 00:17:01.000
Teacher! I need to borrow 
a blanket and a towel!

249
00:17:16.430 --> 00:17:19.890
By the way, I haven't seen 
Hananoi-san around recently.

250
00:17:19.890 --> 00:17:21.390
That's because...

251
00:17:22.100 --> 00:17:23.810
<i>You</i> got in a fight, Hotaru?!

252
00:17:23.810 --> 00:17:25.890
I didn't even know you could get mad!

253
00:17:25.890 --> 00:17:29.860
I honestly don't know if 
I could face him right now.

254
00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:33.440
<i>I've never yelled at someone
 like that before.</i>

255
00:17:33.990 --> 00:17:36.490
Oh. Look who's here.

256
00:17:52.170 --> 00:17:53.880
Hotaru-chan.

257
00:17:54.130 --> 00:17:55.470
Hananoi-kun.

258
00:17:56.380 --> 00:17:59.890
I'm sorry I've been bugging you so much.
 I won't bother you after today.

259
00:18:00.140 --> 00:18:03.640
But before that, I wanted to give you this.

260
00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:08.020
Oh, don't worry. I went back 
after the snow melted.

261
00:18:08.770 --> 00:18:13.650
Thank you. It was a present from my family.

262
00:18:14.440 --> 00:18:16.650
Did you know it was important to me?

263
00:18:16.950 --> 00:18:23.790
No, but I did notice you seem to have special
things that you like to use all the time.

264
00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:27.540
So I thought you'd be sad if you lost it.

265
00:18:29.330 --> 00:18:30.670
<i>I see...</i>

266
00:18:31.040 --> 00:18:38.090
<i>Hananoi-kun treasures what's important 
to me. Even more than I do.</i>

267
00:18:38.800 --> 00:18:43.390
<i>If that's what it means to love, then...</i>

268
00:18:44.600 --> 00:18:47.730
<i>it's truly a wonderful thing.</i>

269
00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:53.440
Hananoi-kun, I have something 
I want to give you too.

270
00:18:53.860 --> 00:18:54.780
Here.

271
00:18:56.990 --> 00:18:59.910
I found it on the ground 
by the vending machine.

272
00:19:01.660 --> 00:19:03.450
Put it on.

273
00:19:08.040 --> 00:19:10.790
Yeah, the other one seemed lonely by itself.

274
00:19:10.790 --> 00:19:12.840
They look better together.

275
00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:16.960
Take good care of what's
 important to you, okay?

276
00:19:18.010 --> 00:19:19.380
I'm really sorry.

277
00:19:19.380 --> 00:19:21.470
<i>Wow, he looks so sad.</i>

278
00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:23.350
<i>But it's kind of cute.</i>

279
00:19:25.970 --> 00:19:31.190
<i>Whenever I'm with Hananoi-kun, 
I keep feeling all kinds of new things.</i>

280
00:19:32.480 --> 00:19:36.730
<i>If I spent more time with him, 
maybe I'd start to understand</i>

281
00:19:37.360 --> 00:19:39.950
<i>what it's like to be overwhelmed with emotion.</i>

282
00:19:40.570 --> 00:19:43.200
<i>What it's like to fall in love.</i>

283
00:19:44.990 --> 00:19:47.700
<i>There's no such thing as someone 
who shouldn't fall in love.</i>

284
00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:53.130
See you.

285
00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:54.840
W-Wait!

286
00:19:56.340 --> 00:20:01.800
U-Um, I don't think I've told you this yet,

287
00:20:01.800 --> 00:20:06.350
but I've never once thought that 
I <i>didn't</i> like you, Hananoi-kun.

288
00:20:06.720 --> 00:20:09.390
I don't think it means 
that I like you in <i>that</i> way,

289
00:20:09.390 --> 00:20:12.730
but it's been fun, and you've 
made me happy sometimes.

290
00:20:13.350 --> 00:20:15.860
So, um...

291
00:20:16.770 --> 00:20:21.070
Do you think someone like 
me might be able to learn?

292
00:20:22.240 --> 00:20:25.570
Do you think even I might 
fall in love someday?

293
00:20:26.490 --> 00:20:28.080
<i>When that girl said...</i>

294
00:20:28.080 --> 00:20:32.120
<i>You'll never be in a proper 
relationship anyway!</i>

295
00:20:32.120 --> 00:20:36.500
<i>I felt like she was talking to me.
It was saddening.</i>

296
00:20:36.840 --> 00:20:40.550
<i>Why don't I ever feel that 
kind of strong emotion?</i>

297
00:20:41.590 --> 00:20:46.510
<i>Why can't I understand what that's like
when everybody else can?</i>

298
00:20:47.350 --> 00:20:48.640
I know you will.

299
00:20:53.020 --> 00:20:55.100
I'm sure that the day will come

300
00:20:55.730 --> 00:20:58.940
when you know how it feels 
to love someone special.

301
00:21:04.740 --> 00:21:05.780
Were you...

302
00:21:06.740 --> 00:21:09.910
Were you serious about giving it a try?

303
00:21:10.450 --> 00:21:11.410
Huh?

304
00:21:12.250 --> 00:21:15.960
Are you... saying you'll go out with me?

305
00:21:19.550 --> 00:21:23.170
I still don't know if I can make it work,

306
00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:28.140
but I want to know what it feels 
like to fall in love with someone!

307
00:21:34.060 --> 00:21:36.270
Um, Hananoi-kun...

308
00:21:36.480 --> 00:21:37.730
Everyone's looking—

309
00:21:37.730 --> 00:21:38.610
I'm so happy.

310
00:21:40.690 --> 00:21:41.690
I'm so happy...

311
00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:50.910
<i>And that's how I ended up
 with my very first boyfriend,</i>

312
00:21:51.620 --> 00:21:55.290
<i>even though I still didn't really 
understand what was happening.</i>

313
00:21:55.840 --> 00:22:01.960
<i>Hananoi-kun's idea of love and my idea 
of love might not be the same thing,</i>

314
00:22:02.800 --> 00:22:07.430
<i>but at the very least,
I've taken my first step into a new world.</i>

315
00:22:04.430 --> 00:22:09.430
